Great 👍 I’ll show you the 2-minute OpenShift Agent Installer troubleshooting workflow that Red Hat engineers use. This works for OCP 4.12–4.18 agent-based installs, including baremetal / telco CNF setups like yours.
Follow these in order. You will quickly identify the exact issue.
🚀 Step 1 — Check Assisted Service Containers (Rendezvous Node)
Run on master1 (20.1.30.150):
Bash
Copy code
podman ps | grep assisted
You should see 3 containers:
Copy code

assisted-service
assisted-db
assisted-image-service
If assisted-db is missing, cluster objects cannot be created.
🚀 Step 2 — Verify InfraEnv Exists
Run on master1:
Bash
Copy code
TOKEN=$(grep USER_AUTH_TOKEN /etc/assisted/rendezvous-host.env | cut -d= -f2)

curl -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" \
http://localhost:8090/api/assisted-install/v2/infra-envs | jq
Expected output:
Copy code

airtelvvt
If output is empty [], then infra-env was never created.
🚀 Step 3 — Check Cluster Object
Run:
Bash
Copy code
curl -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" \
http://localhost:8090/api/assisted-install/v2/clusters | jq
Expected:
Copy code

name: airtelvvt
status: ready
If status is:
Copy code

insufficient
hosts are not registered yet.
🚀 Step 4 — Check Hosts Registration
Run:
Bash
Copy code
curl -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" \
http://localhost:8090/api/assisted-install/v2/hosts | jq
Expected output:
Copy code

master1
master2
master3
If you only see master1, then master2 and master3 are not joining.
🚀 Step 5 — Check Agent Logs (Worker Nodes)
Run on master2 or master3:
Bash
Copy code
journalctl -u agent.service -n 50
Healthy output shows:
Copy code

Host registered
Inventory sent
Connected to assisted-service
If you see loops like:
Copy code

Querying assisted-service for infra-env-id
then the node cannot retrieve infra-env.
🚀 Step 6 — Verify Assisted API Connectivity
From master2:
Bash
Copy code
curl http://20.1.30.150:8090/api/assisted-install/v2/infra-envs
If you get:
Copy code

401 unauthenticated
That is good (API reachable).
If you get timeout, then networking issue.
🚀 Step 7 — Verify Network Interfaces
Agent install fails silently if NIC names mismatch.
Run on each node:
Bash
Copy code
ip link
Your config expects:
Copy code

ens1f0
ens4f0
If the server shows something like:
Copy code

eno1
ens2f0
then bonding fails → agent cannot send inventory.
🚀 Step 8 — Verify Time Sync
Time mismatch can break token authentication.
Run on all nodes:
Bash
Copy code
timedatectl
Ensure:
Copy code

System clock synchronized: yes
🚀 Step 9 — Check Agent Inventory
On master2 run:
Bash
Copy code
ls /var/log/agent
and:
Bash
Copy code
cat /var/log/agent/agent.log
Look for:
Copy code

failed to send inventory
authentication error
infraenv not found
🚀 Step 10 — Watch Installation Start
When everything works, master1 log shows:
Bash
Copy code
journalctl -u assisted-service.service -f
You will see:
Copy code

Host registered
Host ready for install
Starting cluster installation
Then:
Copy code

Bootstrapping cluster
